The main opposition party, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has urged the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) to immediately stop collation and further announcement of Results of the presidential election held on Saturday, February 23. In a statement issued at a press conference and made available to Sundiata Post on Tuesday, Tanimu Turaki, SAN, Deputy Director-General (Admin) of the PDP Presidential Campaign Organisation, also demanded cancellation of election results from Yobe, Zamfara, Borno and Nasarawa states. The full statement reads: The main opposition party, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has urged the Independent National Electoral… The main opposition party, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has urged the Independent National Electoral… ....Calls For Fresh Elections In Borno, Yobe, Others By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -…